# Trading Chart Analysis

## 1. DRAWN ZONES & RECTANGLES

**Left Diagram (Schematic):**
- Red/pink shaded rectangle at upper peak labeled "BUY-SIDE LIQUIDITY"
- Red/pink shaded rectangle at lower trough labeled "SELL SIDE LIQUIDITY"

**Right Diagram (Actual Chart):**
- Light blue/gray horizontal rectangle in upper portion of consolidation range labeled "BUY-SIDE LIQUIDITY"
- Light blue/gray horizontal rectangle in lower portion of consolidation range labeled "SELL-SIDE LIQUIDITY"
- Red/pink shaded vertical rectangle at top right (above consolidation)
- Red/pink shaded vertical rectangle at bottom right (below consolidation)

## 2. LABELED PRICE LEVELS

No specific price level numbers are visible on the chart.

## 3. TEXT ANNOTATIONS & NOTES

**Main Title:**
"LIQUIDITY ABOVE/BELOW CONSOLIDATION"

**Explanatory Text:**
"WHEN THE PRICE IS GOING SIDEWAYS (CONSOLIDATING) THE LIQUIDITY (RETAIL STOPS) ARE BUILDING ABOVE & BELOW IT, AND IN MOST CASES PRICE WILL WANT TO SWEEP BOTH SIDES BEFORE PICKING A DIRECTION."

**Left Diagram Labels:**
- "BUY-SIDE LIQUIDITY" (upper zone)
- "SELL SIDE LIQUIDITY" (lower zone)

**Right Diagram Labels:**
- "BUY-SIDE LIQUIDITY" (upper zone)
- "SELL-SIDE LIQUIDITY" (lower zone)

## 4. ICT CONCEPT MARKERS

**Liquidity Markers:**
- BUY-SIDE LIQUIDITY zones marked above consolidation ranges
- SELL-SIDE LIQUIDITY zones marked below consolidation ranges

The chart demonstrates liquidity sweep concept where price targets both sides of a consolidation range before directional movement.

## 5. FIBONACCI LEVELS

None visible.

## 6. ARROWS & DIRECTIONAL INDICATORS

**Left Diagram:**
- Upward arrow showing price movement from consolidation into buy-side liquidity zone
- Downward arrow showing price movement from consolidation into sell-side liquidity zone

## 7. TIME/SESSION MARKERS

None visible.

## 8. STRUCTURAL ELEMENTS

**Left Diagram:**
- Simplified line chart showing swing structure with peaks and troughs
- Horizontal consolidation zone indicated in middle section

**Right Diagram:**
- Candlestick chart showing actual price action
- Clear consolidation range with horizontal boundaries
- Price wicks extending into both liquidity zones above and below the range
